                <h4>Complementary Courses (57 credits)</h4>

    
              <p>Below is a list of approved courses.  Additional courses may be substituted with the approval of the Program Director.</p>
<p>21 credits, of which 12 credits must be in the study of a language other than English;</p>
<p>9 credits, at least 3 credits from two of the following lists:</p>
    
      
      
