                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/east-457" class="program-course-title">
              EAST 457 Brushwork in Chinese Painting (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-22134" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: East Asian Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Asian Language &amp; Literature              : The seminar takes an in-depth look at the function and meaning of the brushwork in traditional Chinese painting. Analysis of paintings will be combined to close readings of theoretical texts in translation.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Jeffrey Moser (Winter)                  </p>

    
