  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Russian (Arts)              : Masterpieces of the Russian stage in the nineteenth and twentieth centuries; the emergence of a uniquely Russian dramatic sensitivity against prevailing European trends; the literary word in a public, political and/or avant-garde forum.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              This course is not scheduled for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

