                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/isla-200" class="program-course-title">
              ISLA 200 Islamic Civilization (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-28382" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Islamic Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Islamic Studies              : An introduction to, and survey of, the religious, literary, artistic, legal, philosophical and scientific traditions that constituted Islamic civilization from the 7th Century until the mid-19th Century.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
