                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/isla-380" class="program-course-title">
              ISLA 380 Islamic Philosophy and Theology (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-28404" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Islamic Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Islamic Studies              : A survey of the most important philosophers and theologians in Islamic intellectual history, with a focus on the theories they articulated and the movements they engendered. The impact of European thought on 19th and 20th century Islamic intellectual history is also examined.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Robert Wisnovsky (Fall)                  </p>

    
