    <p>
      Art History              : Paintings, prints, sculpture and architecture produced in Europe in the 'long' eighteenth century, with an emphasis on major artists. Themes include the teaching of art and its display, the emergence of 'publics' for art, and eighteenth-century aesthetics.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Matthew Hunter (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Restriction: Not open to students who have taken ARTH 334.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
