                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/hist-460" class="program-course-title">
              HIST 460 Milton in Myth and History (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-27754" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: History and Classical Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      History              : The great poet-revolutionary as construed or caricatured by contemporaries, and posthumous fans and foes such as Voltaire, Dr Johnson, the Romantics, Whigs, Unitarians, Victorian feminists, Marxists, Bolsheviks, and ex-Marxists.          </p>

